Popular actress Uche Jombo Rodriguez has argued that talent is never enough for anyone in life. The Nollywood star made this known while weighing in on the rape and assault allegations levelled against Manchester United player, Mason Greenwood. “Talent is never enough, character matters. Being an actual human matter,” she tweeted.   Kenneth Okonkwo commends lady for accepting proposal on knee     Giving everyone access unhealthy – Mercy Johnson     Nollywood stars celebrate Abdulateef Adedimeji at 36   Jombo-Rodriguez also gave successful tips on being successful as a producer. - Advertisement - She said; “A logline is about selling your story not telling it. Yes, you can write a brilliant script and not be able to write a good logline for it. It’s ok to ask for help.” The mother of one also revealed one of her favourite films. “Holding Hope, one of my favourite films of mine.” Jombo-Rodriguez co-produced the film, ‘Holding Hope,’ alongside Emem Isong in 2010. The film was written by Uduak Isong Oguamanam and directed by Desmond Elliot. It featured Desmond Elliot, Uche Jombo, Nadia Buari, and Abiola Segun Williams.